The paper proposes a novel algorithm for Nonnegative Tensor Factorization (NTF) which is a popular technique in machine learning and data analysis. The paper discusses the limitations of existing factorization algorithms and proposes a new approach that is scalable in terms of tensor size, density, and rank. The paper also uses Lipschitz continuity to calculate element importance and proposes a saturation point based element selection method. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
